<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:25:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T18:26:00-05:00" n="951" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                    <head>Kasimer Pfyffer</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:34" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:34">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">To the Editor of the Bund, in Berne:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Honored Sir</hi>: As the undersigned had not the good
                        fortune to see the address of sympathy and condolence to the American Union,
                        being absent from his place of residence while it was circulating,
                        respectfully requests you to add his name to the list of signers to that
                        patriotic document.</p>
                    <p>I remain yours, with much esteem,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>KASIMIR PFYFFER.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>